page.title: 01INTRODUCTION TO FLEETWOOD
page.content: Our twelve kilometre square block varies greatly,from the industrial and residential areas in the west,to the farmlands and marshlands across the {River Wyre}.The River Wyre is a clear dividing stretch between the two areas.On the{Fleetwood}side of the River Wyre is the most heavily populated square kilometre block.On this side the road system is good,as are the educational,shopping, recreational and general service facilities. However across the Wyre,the emphasis is on farms and marshland.The population is very sparse,and to find employment here is very difficult.The area on a whole is very flat.The River Wyre which flows from the Forest of Bowland to Fleetwood,is at it's widest part in our block.
